Wang Yang, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, who is also in charge of coordinating the CPC Central Committee's work on Xinjiang, presides over the seventh national meeting on pairing-assistance to Xinjiang in Hotan, northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region. The meeting was held from Sunday to Tuesday. (Photo: Xinhua)  
